# Negative Feedback Loops

> [!Ontology]-
> up:: [[Cards/Feedback Loops\|Feedback Loops]], [[Cards/Homeostasis\|Homeostasis]]
> jump:: [[Cards/Positive Feedback Loops\|Positive Feedback Loops]]
> down:: 

> [!Definition] Definition
> A negative feedback loop is a process in which the output of a system influences its own input, tending to reduce fluctuations and maintain homeostasis.
